tinycthread
------------------------------------------
TinyCThread is a minimalist, portable, threading library for C, intended to
make it easy to create multi threaded C applications.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libtinycthread-devel-1.2+git20161001-1bl1
  libtinycthread0-1.2+git20161001-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tinycthread/tinycthread

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/tinycthread/tinycthread.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack tinycthread-1.2+git20161001-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./tinycthread-1.2+git20161001-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/tinycthread-1.2+git20161001-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/tinycthread-1.2+git20161001-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtinycthread0-1.2+git20161001-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtinycthread-devel-1.2+git20161001-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(tinycthread)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/tinycthread.README
  /usr/share/doc/tinycthread/README.txt

(libtinycthread0)
  /usr/bin/cygtinycthread-0.dll

(libtinycthread-devel)
  /usr/include/tinycthread.h
  /usr/lib/libtinycthread.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/tinycthread.pc

------------------

